  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol compliance implementation in envoyproxy/envoy is found across multiple C++ source files. The primary implementation is in source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h and .cc, which contains the GrpcHealthCheckerFactory and GrpcHealthCheckerImpl classes. The GrpcHealthCheckerImpl class implements the grpc.health.v1.Health service's Check method by creating GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession instances that manage the health check lifecycle.\n\nThe implementation follows the gRPC health check protocol as defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto (from the grpc repository). The key protocol elements are:\n\n1. **HealthCheckRequest Handling** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc, line 233-238): The GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::onInterval method constructs a grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest message with an optional service name and sends it to the upstream endpoint via HTTP/2.\n\n2. **HealthCheckResponse Status Mapping** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc, lines 300-312, 365-398): The isHealthCheckSucceeded method checks if the gRPC status is OK and the response status is SERVING. The logHealthCheckStatus method logs the health check response status, mapping grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::ServingStatus values (SERVING, NOT_SERVING, UNKNOWN, SERVICE_UNKNOWN) to descriptive strings.\n\n3. **gRPC Status Mapping** (source/common/grpc/status.cc): The Grpc::Utility::httpToGrpcStatus function maps HTTP response codes to gRPC status codes according to https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md. The GrpcHealthCheckerImpl uses this mapping in decodeHeaders (line 109) when handling non-200 HTTP responses.\n\n4. **Message Serialization/Deserialization** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc, lines 130-162, 151-159): The decodeData method uses Grpc::Decoder (source/common/grpc/codec.h) to parse incoming gRPC frames containing HealthCheckResponse protobuf messages. The response is deserialized into grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse (line 151).\n\n5. **gRPC Response Header Processing** (source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc, lines 96-128): The decodeHeaders method validates gRPC response headers using Grpc::Common::isGrpcResponseHeaders, checks for appropriate gRPC status in both headers and trailers using Grpc::Common::getGrpcStatus, and handles HTTP to gRPC status mapping for non-200 responses.\n\n6. **Health Discovery Service Integration** (source/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.cc, lines 49-55): The HdsDelegate class supports reporting health check capabilities including HTTP and TCP protocols, with infrastructure for managing health checks across multiple clusters.\n\nThe configuration for gRPC health checks is defined in api/envoy/config/core/v3/health_check.proto (message GrpcHealthCheck), which allows specifying a service name, authority header override, and initial metadata headers for health check requests.\n\nKey supporting utilities include Grpc::Common (source/common/grpc/common.cc) for header parsing and status extraction, and Grpc::Decoder (source/common/grpc/codec.h) for wire protocol frame decoding."
}

